    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-05-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-05-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="258"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d258">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/1776</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the High
                        Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Russell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-05-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 7, 1925</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 254</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your despatch No. 459 of November
                    21, 1924,<note n="17" xml:id="d258fn17">Not printed.</note> in relation to the
                    request for arbitration on the question of whether the Haitian Loan of 1910 is
                    payable in gold, the Department informs you that it has beeen asked by the
                    French Embassy on behalf of the Banque de l’Union Parisienne to use its good
                    offices in an effort to induce the Haitian Government to consent to such
                    arbitration.</p>
                <pb facs="0397" n="315" xml:id="pg_315"/>
                <p>After carefully considering the matter, the Department has definitely declined to
                    grant this request of the French Government and has sent to the French Embassy a
                    note embodying such refusal, a copy of which is enclosed for your
                        information.<note n="18" xml:id="d258fn18">Printed <hi rend="italic"
                            >supra.</hi>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leland Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
